Coming up on 21 September is the Full Moon in Pisces, and with Mabon/Ostara coming up the day after, it makes for a busy time!

Thanks to Pisces, it’s a time where you might find your emotions on a bit of a rollercoaster, so buckle up!

Like the water sign Pisces, it’s best to try and go with the flow and ride the tides rather than reacting or try to control them. This is easier said than done though!

Are you ready?! I’m feeling it already!

Lindsay 💜

In only a few days, Mabon will be celebrated in the northern hemisphere and Ostara will be celebrated in the southern hemisphere.

Mabon is also known at the Autumn Equinox and Ostara, the Spring Equinox. They mark a point in the year where there is balance between the hours of light and the hours of dark. 

Are you ready?!

Lindsay 💜

node.text:
✨ O𝕣𝕒𝕔𝕝𝕖 R𝕖𝕧𝕖𝕒𝕝 ✨ 
1. S𝕠𝕨𝕖𝕝𝕠 
This rune is about wholeness, success, and positive change. Sometimes we can loose connection with ourselves amongst the busyness of life, but this rune is about reconnecting with who you  truly are. You might feel the need to spend more time alone, so honour those feelings. It’s a form of self care that’s necessary, even if spending time alone is challenging for you. It will be worth it to rebalance and feed your soul as well as reconnect with yourself.

2. J𝕖𝕣𝕒
This is a very positive rune. It represents a process of working towards a goal as well as the harvest when you reach that goal. It brings much hope for the future as well as a sense of peace and prosperity. All the hard work you’ve been putting in lately - whether it be a project, your job, with family or working on yourself - will start to pay off. This is encouragement to keep going. It’s also a reminder not to rush, but rather taking time to enjoy the process of reaching your goal, knowing you will achieve your goal in the end.

3. T𝕙𝕦𝕣𝕚𝕤𝕒𝕫
This rune asks you to step out of your comfort zone. This might sound scary, but have courage, as it’s necessary for your personal growth. The unknown can be daunting, but don’t let the fears win as they can stop you from moving forward and growing. You may have been giving your energy away to others a lot lately but this is a reminder to take your energy back to reclaim your power. It’s necessary for your mental, physical and spiritual health.

✨ T𝕙𝕣𝕚𝕗𝕥𝕪 S𝕥𝕒𝕣𝕥𝕖𝕣 T𝕠𝕠𝕝𝕤 ✨
When it comes to starting out in your Craft, you don’t need to spend a fortune gathering together everything you might possibly need. 

Here’s a few basic items that would be incredibly useful - and the good news is they are all inexpensive to buy, and you might already have them around in your home!

Researching and learning are the foundations of a Witch’s Craft but books can be really expensive. Second hand books are a good way to cut down cost. Ebooks tend to be even cheaper, so are another more affordable option. As for free materials, it’s possible to find free Witchcraft books on places like Google Books and some can even be downloaded as PDFs. 

Lindsay 💜

Good morning, lovelies! Happy Friday! I can feel the weather turning as I sit here in the garden drinking my first cup of coffee of the day 🍁🍂

Today, I’m using my rune deck today for our oracle reading of the week 😊

Take a moment to sit and meditate on the cards and crystals above. Choose the cards that draw your eye or call to you. ⁣

If you feel you want to chose based on the crystals, go with your intuition! If you feel you can’t choose, maybe all three cards are calling you! ⁣
⁣
Check back later today when I’ll post the reveal and full readings for each card! ⁣

Have a wonderful day! 
Lindsay 💜

node.text:
🍎A𝕡𝕡𝕝𝕖𝕤 & M𝕒𝕓𝕠𝕟🍎
Apples are a common symbol of Mabon/Autumn Equinox. In magickal terms they are mostly associated with abundance, health and well being, knowledge, self-knowledge, setting seeds of intention, fertility and love.

The great thing is that apples can be incorporated into your craft practically in so many. You can pick them, cook with them, use them as decoctions and they can be used as an offering to give thanks for the harvest by burying them. The good thing is, many of these are broom closet friendly making them easier to incorporate into your craft if you’re unable to practice openly.

What’s your favourite way to use apples at this time of year?

Lindsay 💜

💦 W𝕒𝕥𝕖𝕣 💦
Last element up is Water. Here’s some info about this element as well as some  correspondence. These items are all things aligned with the Water so can be incorporated in to spells or rituals to help you connect more with this element.

Left to right in the graphic represents: direction, the qualities of  Water, zodiac signs, colours, crystals, herbs, physical items that can be used to symbolise Water, planets.

This is the element I have the most trouble connecting with as I can’t get past the fear of deep water I’ve had all my life. 
Do you connect with Water?
